<exercise>
  <statement>
    <p>
      Find the number of ways of choosing 4 cards from a pack of 52 playing cards. In how many of these 
      <ol marker ="i.">
        <li>
          <p>
            4 cards are of the same suit?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            4 cards belong to four different suits?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            4 cards are face cards?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            2 cards are red and 2 cards are black?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            cards are of the same color?
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
  </statement>
  <hint>
    <p>
      There are 13 cards in each suit <em>Diamond, Heart, Club, and Spade.</em>
      <ol marker ="i.">
        <li>
          <p>
          <m>  ^{13}C_4 +  ^{13}C_4 +  ^{13}C_4 + ^{13}C_4 = ----</m>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
           <m> ^{13}C_1 \times  ^{13}C_1 \times  ^{13}C_1 \times ^{13}C_1 = ----</m>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
           <m> ^{12}C_4 = ----</m>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
           <m> ^{26}C_2 \times  ^{26}C_2  = ----</m>
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            <m> ^{26}C_4 +  ^{26}C_4  = ----</m>
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
  </hint>
</exercise>

